verses.roman:
jagannāthera āge cāri sampradāya gāya
dui pāśe dui, pāche eka sampradāya

synonyms: jagannāthera āge—in front of the Deity Lord Jagannātha; cāri sampradāya gāya—four groups were chanting; dui pāśe—on two sides; dui—another two groups; pāche—at the rear; eka sampradāya—another group.
translation: Four parties chanted and danced in front of Lord Jagannātha, and on both sides were two other parties. Another was at the rear.
